title: $:/plugins/crosseye/json-convert/usage/editor/fields-tables
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Below the records path sit two tables joined visually but distinct in
storage:

* ''TiddlyWiki Fields'' — `title`, `tags`, `caption`, `text` plus a pill row for adding common standard fields (`author`, `color`, `created`, …) and a ''more…'' toggle for the long tail (`_canonical_uri`, `bag`, …).
* ''Custom Fields'' — adds rows on demand via the ''Add'' button in the section header.  Each row's //name// is editable inline.  Duplicate detection (vs other custom names and vs TW field names) is live.

''Row states.''  Each row has two visual modes:

* ''Display'' — name + value + transform shown as plain text, with ''Edit'' and ''×'' buttons.  Validation problems flag the row with a red left edge; the inline error appears in edit mode.
* ''Edit'' — name (custom rows only), value, and transform become editable; a ''Browse…'' button appears next to the value.  Click ''Done'' to collapse back to display.

Pills and ''Add'' open the new row directly into edit mode with the cursor
ready for the value.
